Some other minor nitpicks/inconsistencies that bothered me while watching:
- Sonic destroys the energy infrastructure of the entire town but phones work. Not just cellphones (despite the effect being so large it turned off satellites) but regular phones too
- Not only does the sheriff guy gets into a commercial building after being hunted as a terrorist, they make a joke about him kidnapping a child and no one really cares
- Sonic sends the sheriff to his hometown at day and a few minutes later when Sonic arrives it's night, despite portal travel being shown as instantaneous and Sonic only racing Robotnik for a few minutes at most

The studio shutting down had nothing to do with the Sonic movie. It was because of market pressures in the Vancouver area and lacking tax breaks.
https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486721/sonic-the-hedgehogs-redesign-studio-is-closing

Direct quote from the article:

A statement from parent company Technicolor cited “increasing external market pressures” in Vancouver as well as “attractive opportunities in other locations” as the reason behind the shuttering of MPC Vancouver.

snippet.textDisplay: When sonic farted (or pretended to fart I couldn't remember) the entire theater went into an absolute uproar, I remember the attendants getting nervous because the amount of laughter coming from the audience was shaking the theater violently to the point that several wall speakers came crashing down. Some people laughed so hard they vomited, the father in the row in front of me blasted this old couple in the handicap seats ahead of him with a horrible mixture of junior mints and popcorn it was a terrible sight but honestly I wasn't focused on that, I was still too busy laughing from sonic farting. After awhile it became a blur but I just remember crying while laughing and I couldn't tell if I was crying tears of pain or what but I remember waking up on the floor and the end credits were already rolling. Overall Id give the movie a 5/10 it was ok.

snippet.textDisplay:
Apparently, the horrifying design was only kept because the execs and higher ups for the film wanted to go for a cheap "realistic appeal", admittedly in the same manner as Transformers and TMNT did, and just refused to listen to the design team on the matter whatsoever. They even expected the ugly design to piss off Sonic fans, and just hoped that all the casual viewers would just let it slide. And when that clearly didn't work, and the entire world was talking about how bad the design was, only then they realized they fucked up.

Although the closure of the studio behind animating Sonic actually had nothing to do with the movie in the first place.
